  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed at the campaign level and is discussed throughout the narrative; however, individual validation result records were not uniformly linked to formal UQ artifacts — several results characterise uncertainty only in prose without a structured hasUncertaintyQuantification reference, leaving aleatory uncertainty uncharacterized at the per-result level. Full 13-factor assessment completed. Decision: Accepted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-vad-class3",
